dct_description_sm: compiled from the M.S. maps in the Colonial Office, Captn. Owen's Survey ; J. & C. Walker, sculpt.
Map of South Africa, with environs of Cape and Graham Towns. Relief is shown in hachures.
Plate 125 from: Maps of the Society for the Diffusion of Useful Knowledge. London : Chapman and Hall, 1844.
Imprint on map: London : Published for the Society for the Diffusion of Useful Knowledge by Chapman & Hall, 186 Stand, April 1st 1834.
